      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The question of starting the\nMain avenue incline into Peaceful\nValley from the west side of the\nMonroe street bridge, instead of\nLincoln street, as at present, was\npresented to the city COUNCIL last\nnight and referred to the street\ncommittee for a recommendation\nThe proposed change in the grade\nwas petitioned for by nearly all of\nthe property owners that travel\nover or are interested in the i'm\nprovement of Main avenue.\n\n\nOn the motion of Councilman\nLambert the board of public works\nwas asked to draft plans and fur\nnish estimates of the cost of a\ntrestle with which to make the fill\nOn Main avenue to bring it to the\ngrade of Monroe street."
    }
  ]
